Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.20,0:00:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David Hawkins. I've been a psychiatrist for the last 35 years,\Npsychoanalyst, nutritionist, researcher into the relationship between nutrition and brain chemistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.20,0:00:23.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The last 10 years I've been doing research on the nature of consciousness itself\Nand its relationship to that which the world calls spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.55,0:00:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This involves the relationship between body, mind, and spirit.\NWhat is the relationship between body, mind, and spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.55,0:00:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And how does it relate to our topic for today, which is how to let go of depression?\NDepression, despondency, that plague of mankind which has been there since ancient biblical days
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.55,0:00:53.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and which today is being called a minor epidemic.\NA minor epidemic with a rising suicide rate amongst young people, especially adolescents.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.55,0:00:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Very timely, very important in all of our lives.\NFew of us have managed to live on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.55,0:01:09.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For any great length of time without experiencing depression.\NMaybe minor in the form of regrets, mourning, loss, loss of loved ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.55,0:01:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of things that we have valued in our life because of their meaning.\NAnd so we're going into that today looking at it from the viewpoint of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.58,0:01:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but we'll also cover what is the place of biochemistry, what is the place of antidepressants.\NAre these the cause or are these the effect of the depression?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.98,0:01:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In talking about this, we'll again have to review what is that relationship between body, mind, and spirit,\Nwhich we'll be talking about because we'll be talking about the treatment
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.53,0:01:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and the understanding of depression on all three levels.\NSo we need to review again, as we have in other talks in this series,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.42,0:02:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the fact that the body has no way of experiencing itself.\NThe body cannot experience its own bodiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.68,0:02:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It cannot experience its own sensations.\NThe body is experienced in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.90,0:02:21.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind, curiously enough, also has no real capacity to experience itself.\NMemories, thoughts, feelings, fantasies of the future, daydreams,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.90,0:02:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all of these are registered and experienced in a field which is larger and more diffuse,\Na field of energy that we call consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.90,0:02:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,A field that is currently being researched with advanced theoretical physics.\NThe relationship of mind to this great field called consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.90,0:02:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness itself, curiously, has to be experienced by something even greater\Nand formless, and that we call awareness.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.06,0:03:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So it is because of awareness that we're aware of what is going on within consciousness.\NConsciousness allows us to know that which is going on in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.06,0:03:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Mind allows us to know that which is going on in our feelings, our emotions, our memory.\NIt allows us to know what the sensations are from the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.38,0:03:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,reporting to us our experience of the body.\NTherefore, all of this is going on within consciousness itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.38,0:03:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And in this, as well as our other talks, we have emphasized the importance of addressing issues,\Nand addressing the highest level, the level where there is the most power,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.38,0:03:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,so that a change on the level of consciousness, a change within mind,\Nbrings about an alteration within the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.48,0:03:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,In talking about depression, that aspect of the part of the body we'll be interested in is the brain.\NThe brain and its hormones and its neurotransmitters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.48,0:03:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and how depression affects the physiology of the brain.\NWhat are the real causes of depression then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.48,0:04:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As we look into that, we will be looking at a map of consciousness,\Nwhich we have been using in this series of talks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.96,0:04:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A mathematical model in which we have levels of consciousness in what we call the box.\NThe levels of consciousness starting from the lowest,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.96,0:04:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which we have calibrated at zero, death,\Nall the way to the highest, calibrated at 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.96,0:04:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is a very high, joyful state,\Nand one beyond which the world calls enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.96,0:04:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Within those levels, you will see that the energy fields have a direction,\Nindicated by the arrows.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.96,0:04:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The indication of the arrows is whether we experience this as a positive asset in our life,\Nor whether it has a negative deleterious effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.96,0:04:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice that in about the middle of the box,\Nat a level called courage, which is calibrated at an energy field of 200,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.15,0:04:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that these energies now,\Nsuddenly go neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.15,0:05:05.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And we notice that those energy fields above the level of courage,\Na level which we cross by telling the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.15,0:05:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,now the energy fields swing to the right and indicate a positive\Nor life-supportive energy field,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.15,0:05:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all the way up to love at 500 and joy at 540.\NThis will be important for us to refer to,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.98,0:05:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a context in which to hold our subject for today,\Nbecause we are going to be talking about the bottom of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.98,0:05:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We are going to be talking about those human experiences,\Nstarting at the bottom called guilt, apathy, grief.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.98,0:05:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,These energy fields expressing themselves in an emotion,\Nself-hatred, self-recrimination, hopelessness, despair, despondency,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.98,0:05:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,all these accompanied by feelings of regret, loss and despondency.\NIn these energy fields of depression then,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:06:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,our view of the world, our view of the world is that it is a sad\Nand hopeless place of sin and suffering.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.62,0:06:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Our view of God then, the God of a world like that,\Nwould be one who is unfeeling, uncaring,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.82,0:06:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,from whom you are separated, who ignores you,\Nor possibly is dead, or at its worst, if he is alive,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.82,0:06:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,would perhaps be the destroyer.\NOut of your guiltiness, worthlessness, sinfulness,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.82,0:06:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a God like that would throw you into hell,\Nabsolute destruction forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.82,0:06:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,When we look over at the process going on in consciousness\Nin these lower energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.07,0:06:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we see coming out of deflated, the one right above it,\Nwe come into one called dispirited,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.07,0:06:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of that energy of life, the desire to live.\NComing lower to this apathy state,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.07,0:06:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that the process going on in consciousness\Nis the loss of energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.07,0:07:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the loss of the life energy within,\Nwhich comes within the being,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.07,0:07:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it no longer attracts energy from the universe,\Nand so our process is one of being de-energized,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.07,0:07:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,leading to the self-hatred of destruction\Nand these states preceding death,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.07,0:07:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,so that out of this we often see a pattern of passive suicide.\NSo today we'll be looking at
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.07,0:07:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,active suicide and passive suicide.\NWhat do they come out of?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.07,0:07:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,How can they be handled?\NWhat do they really mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.07,0:07:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In what way can we create an understanding\Nof this whole field of depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.07,0:07:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,this plague of mankind?\NHow can we benefit from an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.30,0:07:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,coming out of the study of the nature of consciousness itself?\NWe notice that all these energy fields below the level of courage
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.87,0:07:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,have a direction,\Nand a negative direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.87,0:08:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And seldom do one of these emotions come through\Nall by themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.87,0:08:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally, one negative emotion tends to pull\Nall of them to some degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.94,0:08:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,so that in depression then,\Nthere is also feelings coming from this level
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.94,0:08:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of self-blame, self-hatred.\NThere's feelings coming from this level
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.94,0:08:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of hopelessness and despair.\NThere's regrets about the past,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.94,0:08:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and fears about the future.\NVery often there is anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and we often hear it said\Nthat depression is anger turned inward.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.67,0:08:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So one way that's recommended in traditional psychotherapy\Nis to try to energize and bring up the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.67,0:08:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,which is accompanying the depression.\NBut then we have to ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.80,0:08:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,so then what is the source of the anger?\NAnd we will find out that both the anger and the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.80,0:08:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,are coming from the same error.\NFrom having made the same mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.80,0:09:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,within the mind, within consciousness itself.\NAnd what is that error which we're going to find,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.99,0:09:07.99,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we look at the anger,\Nwe look at the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.99,0:09:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,we look at the grief, the apathy, the guilt.\NWe'll find that for some reason
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.99,0:09:17.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the person has placed their survival\Non something outside of themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.99,0:09:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that all these energy fuels here,\Nwhich are in this direction,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.02,0:09:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,are based on placing the source of your happiness\Nas something outside of oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.02,0:09:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes from having been vulnerable.\NIt comes from being the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.02,0:09:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Being the victim, being at the effect of\Na cause that we see as being outside
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.57,0:09:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of our own consciousness.\NWe put the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.57,0:09:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow out into the world.\NAnd so that vulnerability to depression
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.57,0:09:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is there, and so long as we\Nput the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.57,0:10:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,as something outside of ourself.\NThat common frailty of human consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.34,0:10:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to say that, well, when I get that degree,\Nthen I'll be successful and happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.34,0:10:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,When I learn that foreign language,\Nwhen I get to move into that apartment,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.46,0:10:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when I get that fur coat,\Nwhen I get that new car,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.46,0:10:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,when I get that PhD,\Nwhen I get my medical license,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.46,0:10:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if I can only get that internship,\Nif I could get that relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.46,0:10:34.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if I could just change that person out there,\Nif I could get my aunt to stop drinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.46,0:10:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,if our company would only come out of the red\Nand go into the black,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.46,0:10:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it is always out there.\NPlacing the source of one's happiness then
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.46,0:10:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of oneself is putting oneself\Nin the vulnerable position to depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.46,0:10:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,anxiety, fear, and a potential loss.\NIt's only by owning ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.14,0:11:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as the source of our happiness,\Nthe experience of our own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.14,0:11:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,independent and beyond that which happens\Nwithin the world that we become immune
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.14,0:11:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to depressive episodes.\NAnd so to understand that,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.49,0:11:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll have to review briefly\Nthis map of consciousness again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.49,0:11:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you who have seen the other talks,\Neach time that we look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.49,0:11:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to be looking at it from a different angle\Nwith a different emphasis.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.49,0:11:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And each time we look at it,\Nit alters our own understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.49,0:11:35.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of the nature of human consciousness.\NAnd so it's never the same every time we look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.49,0:11:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,because we're coming at it from a different context\Nnow with a broader understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.49,0:11:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we look at it again and we'll see,\Nas we said before, that these energy fields
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.29,0:11:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,are calibrated as to their energy,\Nthe relative energy and power of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.29,0:11:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That they have either a negative direction\Nor a positive direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.29,0:11:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And that there's a crucial crossover\Nin the middle at the level of courage,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.29,0:12:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,which we said is crossed over by the telling of the truth.\NIn this case, the telling of the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.42,0:12:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is that my happiness does not depend\Non anything outside of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.42,0:12:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself, by my own inner decision,\Nby my own integrity, by my intentions,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.42,0:12:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way I see myself and my relationship\Nto the events of life,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.42,0:12:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,am the source of my own happiness.\NAnd so at the bottom we have maximum victimhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In which the total source of one's happiness,\Nthe total source of one's happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.96,0:12:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,has been placed outside of oneself.\NThe loss of that brings about self-contempt,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.96,0:12:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,self-hatred, there is nothing within the self now to love\Nbecause that which was loved
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.96,0:12:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,was seen as something outside of oneself.\NThe stage above that with an energy field of apathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.41,0:12:56.41,Default,,0,0,0,,which we know as hopelessness and despair,\Nis a state of no energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.41,0:13:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,So that a person in that state,\Nwe would say, is in a severe clinical depression.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.41,0:13:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The person is usually unresponsive.\NThey sit in the chair and stare blankly out the window,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.41,0:13:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,very often unresponsive,\Ninto any communication, unable to talk,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.41,0:13:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,very often stop eating,\Nmay not be able to sleep,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.41,0:13:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to function in the world.\NThose are the severe depressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.63,0:13:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And these people, of course, are seeing their life as sad,\Nthey see the future as hopeless,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.63,0:13:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,they see themselves as empty and worthless.\NTheir conception of God, as we've mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the God of that kind of a world\Nis a God who ignores you and doesn't care for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.63,0:13:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a state of total unlovingness,\Nfeeling unloved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.40,0:13:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Our clinical experience indicates that these lower three states,\Nwhich collectively we call despondency and depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.40,0:13:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,come out of the failure\Nto have handled the energy field above it,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.40,0:14:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,which we call fear.\NThe facing of the underlying fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.26,0:14:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the depression is coming about\Nfrom the loss of meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.26,0:14:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So it isn't the things outside of ourself\Nthat we've placed our happiness on,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.26,0:14:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the difficulty,\Nit's the meaning that we have attached to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.26,0:14:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't the PhD degree,\Nit's the meaning of that PhD degree.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.26,0:14:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that relationship,\Nit's the meaning of that relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.26,0:14:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It isn't that position or title as president of the company,\Nor financial success,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.26,0:14:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,or having the right address.\NIt's the meaning,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.74,0:14:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,the way in which we held those things,\Ntheir importance and their value.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.74,0:14:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What we projected onto that,\Nthe way we hold it now then,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.80,0:14:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,depends on the meaning that we have given it.\NIn and of itself, it has no meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.80,0:14:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In and of itself, it merely is.\NSo meaning is a construction.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.80,0:15:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A mental construction\Nthat we have projected out onto
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.80,0:15:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,by giving a thing value.\NThe value then is coming out of our own consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.80,0:15:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,projected onto something that we are seeing\Nas outside of ourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.80,0:15:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing oneself as separated\Nfrom the source of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.96,0:15:23.96,Default,,0,0,0,,There is myself,\Nand then there is that outside myself
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.96,0:15:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from which I feel separated.\NThen the fantasy that if I could reunite with that,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.96,0:15:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,have that, control it,\Nthen that would heal
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.96,0:15:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the inner feeling of lack and separation.\NTo feel separated from that which one wants
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.96,0:15:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is to feel separated from God.\NSo that over here the view of God then
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.96,0:15:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in these depressed states\Nis that you are totally separated
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.96,0:15:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,from the source of your happiness.\NAs we move out of depression into fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.41,0:15:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,the way to get out of the depression then\Nis to look at the underlying fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.41,0:16:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the fear?\NLet's take the woman rocking back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.50,0:16:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in her chair staring out the window\Nwho got the telegram from the State Department
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.50,0:16:13.63,Default,,0,0,0,,that her son was killed in action.\NAnd we said in another talk on this subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.63,0:16:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is actually clinically\Nan example of what actually happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.63,0:16:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,is within several weeks she got a telegram\Nfrom the State Department stating that it was a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.63,0:16:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the serial number was off by one day.\NAnd curiously enough the name had been the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.63,0:16:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they corrected the error\Nand the State Department regretted
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.63,0:16:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the previous telegram.\NSo when the family told her this,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.63,0:16:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,she just kept on rocking back and forth\Nand staring out the window.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.76,0:16:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mother, mother, they all shook her and said,\Ndidn't you hear? Joey is not dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.76,0:16:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's alive. He's fine.\NHe's in an R&R camp in Vietnam.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.76,0:16:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And she kept on rocking back and forth.\NSo that something had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.76,0:16:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, something had happened.\NThe energy field then, the state,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.89,0:17:02.89,Default,,0,0,0,,she had obviously been holding her son\Nand her relationship to her son
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.89,0:17:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,as a source, a major source of happiness,\Nbeing a widow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.89,0:17:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That relationship was prime in her life.\NNow something had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.02,0:17:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The energy of the field had now brought about\Na change in the brain chemistry.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.02,0:17:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we see that the shift in brain chemistry now\Nis a consequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.02,0:17:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It was due to the loss of the meaning in her life.\NThis energy field then expresses itself
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.66,0:17:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,on the level of brain chemistry.\NWe said all things are physical,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.66,0:17:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,mental, and spiritual.\NSpiritually, the meaning here,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.66,0:17:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the separation from God.\NEmotionally, the significance of this relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.66,0:17:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And now on the physical level,\Nin the brain chemistry,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.66,0:17:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,there was a shift.\NThere was a loss of neurotransmitters.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.66,0:17:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So we see in the brain then,\Nin a depressive condition,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.66,0:17:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a depression of essential neurotransmitters,\Nin certain areas of the brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.66,0:18:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And this accompanies the depression.\NAnd it's possible then to ameliorate
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.66,0:18:07.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the expression of this symptom\Non the physical level
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.66,0:18:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,by the use of antidepressants.\NAnd in treating all these conditions,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.66,0:18:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we find it most efficacious to treat them\Nall levels simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.66,0:18:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To address the person in a dialogue\Nwhere they begin to examine
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.66,0:18:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,how they have placed meaning and significance\Nfill the emptiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.66,0:18:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,internal emptiness of their life\Nwith things from the outside
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.66,0:18:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to give it meaning and significance.\NThereby creating this vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.69,0:18:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The way it's held psychologically.\NAnd at the same time to treat it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.69,0:18:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,on the physical level.\NSo the antidepressants nowadays
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.69,0:18:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,are very effective.\NThe side effects are easy to watch for and control.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.69,0:18:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Generally it is a very safe thing\Nto treat pharmacologically.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.69,0:18:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And the antidepressants are very effective.\NOften used in combinations
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.69,0:18:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps with some other drugs such as lithium.\NThey're extremely effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.69,0:19:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,They take the person out of the bottom of the box\Nand lift them up to a higher state.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.69,0:19:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So that in a higher state\Nthey're then able to respond to psychotherapy
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.69,0:19:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,or spiritual counseling\Nto try and alleviate the conditions
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.69,0:19:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that brought about this vulnerability.\NFacing the fear then,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.17,0:19:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,facing the fear\Nthat underlies the depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.17,0:19:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,relieves the depression.\NAnd what is the fear?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.17,0:19:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear is I have lost the meaning of my life.\NI have lost that which is of value.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.30,0:19:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And it will never be replaced.\NSee depression, hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.30,0:19:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,means that the expectation of the future is zero.\NThere is no hope that meaning and significance
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.30,0:19:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that a context will be recreated\Nthat will re-energize
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.30,0:19:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and give one's life meaning again.\NThis of course is an illusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.55,0:19:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the time the hopelessness\Nis based on this perspective,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.55,0:20:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,this perception of one's self\Nand one's relationship to life.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to face the fear.\NSo when we have a depressed person
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.55,0:20:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we look to see what is the loss here.\NThe loss of the job,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.55,0:20:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of vitality,\Nthe loss of youth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.55,0:20:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,People become depressed.\NMiddle age, the loss of opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.55,0:20:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They see middle age as\Nlife having passed them by
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.55,0:20:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and now they've lost their opportunity.\NThe loss of looks to a person
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.55,0:20:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in whom their looks\Nhas been very important in their life
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.55,0:20:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and their way of relating\Nand their sense of self-value.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.55,0:20:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,The middle-aged woman\Nwho feels she is losing her looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.55,0:20:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And if she is based on her power in the world\Nand valued that greatly,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.55,0:20:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,then the loss of the looks to her\Nis a great danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.55,0:20:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And not just a superficial thing\Nsuch as vanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.55,0:20:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's far more than that.\NIt's her whole sense of self-worth and value.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.55,0:20:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Beauty to her has become\Nthat which is valuable
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.55,0:20:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and makes her a worthwhile person.\NSo we look to see
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.55,0:20:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the underlying fear\Nand we get the person
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.55,0:21:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to be willing to look at this fear.\NInstead of depression,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.00,0:21:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,now what the person has to handle is fear.\NBecause fear has to do with the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.00,0:21:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How am I going to live\Nwithout this which has given my life significance?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.00,0:21:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We see this in the addictions, for instance.\NYou might say
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.00,0:21:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that anybody who gets depressed\Nhas been addicted.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.00,0:21:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Addicted to what?\NAddicted to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.00,0:21:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,placing their survival\Non something outside of themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.13,0:21:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,In the addiction,\Nif we threaten to take away
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.13,0:21:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is outside of themself,\Nthe person has been placing their survival
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.13,0:21:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,on happiness, in this case the drug,\Nwe see terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.13,0:21:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only fear, but absolute terror.\NThe conviction within
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.13,0:21:47.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that it will be impossible to live in this world\Nwithout access to that substance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.13,0:21:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have the person look at the fear\Nand then utilize the time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.13,0:21:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the techniques, clinically,\Nthat we have found handle fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.29,0:21:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to be with the fear.\NStop labeling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.32,0:22:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop the thoughts.\NFocus instead on the exact experience
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.32,0:22:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is coming up\Nas one looks at
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.32,0:22:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is feared within mind.\NTo look at that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.32,0:22:15.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and then to go into the radical truth\Nof what is literally being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.32,0:22:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,within oneself.\NAnd the willingness to surrender to that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.32,0:22:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and to let go resisting the fear.\NAs this happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:23.80,0:22:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the sensations run through the body.\NI say to the person,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.80,0:22:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,what are you experiencing in your body?\NMy mouth is so dry I can hardly talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.80,0:22:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,My heart feels like it's fluttering.\NMy stomach feels like it's turning over.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.80,0:22:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel cramps in my abdomen.\NMy knees are so weak I can hardly stand up.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.06,0:22:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we start with them one by one.\NWe say, all right,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.06,0:22:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,the tingling in your legs and your knees,\Ncould you let go resisting that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.06,0:22:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you just let yourself experience that\Nand be with that?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.06,0:22:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you feeling here?\NJust sense what you're sensing.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.06,0:23:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you sensing?\NWell, I'm sensing a tingling in my legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.06,0:23:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I say, can you handle a tingling in your legs?\NYou've handled headaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.66,0:23:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You've handled major surgery.\NYou've handled deaths in the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.66,0:23:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain you can handle a tingling in your legs.\NAnd the person will say, yes, I can handle that.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.66,0:23:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, okay, let go resisting the tingling in the legs.\NNow, how about the cramps in the abdomen?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.73,0:23:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you let go resisting that?\NRight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.73,0:23:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you stop calling them cramps?\NCan you let go resisting that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.73,0:23:28.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.\NLet's go up higher.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.95,0:23:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What about the flip-flops in the stomach?\NCan you handle that?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.95,0:23:36.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I can handle that.\NCan you just handle the experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.95,0:23:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,stop calling it flip-flops in your stomach?\NHow about the beating of your pulse?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.95,0:23:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you let go wanting to resist that?\NJust let your pulse beat away if it wants to.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.95,0:23:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the dry mouth?\NAnd so we get the person to realize,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.95,0:23:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, I can handle that.\NAnd we agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.95,0:23:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody can handle fearful thoughts.\NThere is no such thing as handling fearful thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.66,0:24:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Fearful thoughts create themselves by the thousands.\NAnd as you handle one whole bank of fearful thoughts,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.66,0:24:05.66,Default,,0,0,0,,a whole new bank will arise.\NI'll be late for the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.66,0:24:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't get on the plane.\NI'll be afraid of the plane.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.66,0:24:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's going to happen on the plane.\NI might go to the bathroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.66,0:24:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, the mind will just create an endless series of fears.\NWhat it can handle is a dry mouth,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.66,0:24:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,tingling in the legs.\NAnd the only thing a person benefits
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.66,0:24:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,is relief of depression.\NThey say, oh, I see I'm not depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.66,0:24:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I see I was terrified of the future,\Nthat I will never find happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.66,0:24:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,without that which I wished,\Nlonged for, desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.66,0:24:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was convinced that I had to have that\Nin order to survive and be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.62,0:24:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when you talk to people\Nwho were convinced of that
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.62,0:24:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and were on sizable doses of drugs,\NI mean, they were really as close to actually
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.62,0:24:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,needing something to survive\Nas anybody could be on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.65,0:24:54.65,Default,,0,0,0,,When they faced the fear of it all,\Nthey found that life was joyful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.65,0:24:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Life was complete. Life was full.\NThey enjoyed life for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.65,0:25:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know it's based on an illusion,\Nand therefore we have the courage
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.65,0:25:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for the patient to take them with us\Nto look at the fear,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.65,0:25:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,like we take the child by the hand.\NWhen I was a kid, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.65,0:25:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,somebody on the block told me about boogeymen.\NAnd so my mother had ridiculed
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.65,0:25:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,boogeymen and ghosts and things like that,\Nbut somehow this kid's convincing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.65,0:25:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, he was five years older than I was,\Nso he knew what he was talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.65,0:25:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So what my mother did is take me by the hand\Nand we went down to the dark basement
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.65,0:25:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,with flashlights and we looked all over for boogeymen.\NSo to have someone with you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.65,0:25:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at this fear then is helpful\Nbecause our child is frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.65,0:25:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our child doesn't understand\Nthe nature of real life in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.65,0:25:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the child comes up and says,\Ngee, without that I won't be able to survive.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.65,0:25:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And very often it has been\Na parent substitute,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.65,0:25:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,which was envisioned as being out there.\NWhat about animals?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.97,0:25:54.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't understand anger\Nbecause it said, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.97,0:25:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as we said before, that depression\Nis anger turned within.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.06,0:26:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the basis of the anger then?\NLet's take somebody who is really
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.16,0:26:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,into survival on something outside of themself.\NAgain, we'll use the attic, let's say.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.16,0:26:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And you threaten to take away his bottle\Nor his supplier, flush his drugs down the toilet.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.16,0:26:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And he goes into a rage.\NNow it's very clear to us
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.16,0:26:19.16,Default,,0,0,0,,what the source of the anger is, is it not?\NThe source of the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.16,0:26:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is exactly the same fantasy,\Nthat the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.16,0:26:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,is something outside of myself.\NI have placed it on some object,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.16,0:26:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,some person, place, or thing.\NThe place,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.42,0:26:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of your happiness\Non something outside of yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.42,0:26:39.42,Default,,0,0,0,,puts you in a negative energy field\Nbecause basically it is a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.42,0:26:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The source of your happiness\Nis not something outside of yourself at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.42,0:26:47.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only when we own\Nthat we are the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.61,0:26:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that the energy field goes\Nin a positive direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.61,0:26:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can move the person then\Nout of depression and despondency,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.61,0:26:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,get them to face the fear,\Nget them to desire something better
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.61,0:27:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,for themself,\Nturn that anger into the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.61,0:27:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,at being victim.\NThe anger instead of at the loss of the object.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.64,0:27:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,See, the endless rationalizations\Nand explanations
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.64,0:27:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,to try and make this anger sound justified.\NThey promised me this,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.64,0:27:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,they signed a contract,\Nthey sent a check
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.64,0:27:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to make it sound good.\NThe source of that is always outside of ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.74,0:27:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the explanations,\Nthe details,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.74,0:27:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the events are only justifications\Nfor this anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.02,0:27:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we use this anger now\Ninstead we turn it at anger
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.02,0:27:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at the vulnerability.\NYou say, now it's time to be angry
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.02,0:27:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at what the real cause was\Nand the real cause was
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.02,0:27:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was brought up in a world\Nwhich taught me to think this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.02,0:27:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was taught that this is the right way to think.\NThis is the way to be angry at.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.02,0:27:56.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That we were taught how to think\Nin a way that set us up
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.02,0:28:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,as potential victim,\Nthe source of happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.02,0:28:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The great American way is success.\NIs it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.02,0:28:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Will success bring us happiness?\NWhere I used to live in the East
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.02,0:28:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was a whole row of millionaires\Nand they routinely committed suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.02,0:28:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and took overdoses\Nand they were not at all immune
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.02,0:28:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to the human vulnerabilities.\NSo worldly success,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.02,0:28:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,what we need to be angry at\Nis what got us to sell ourselves out
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.02,0:28:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and how did we sell ourselves out\Nand then to take pride in the fact
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.02,0:28:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are willing to look at this.\NMove up to the courage
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.02,0:28:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to tell the truth about it.\NThe truth is
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.02,0:28:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,something within our consciousness\Nset us up to be vulnerable.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.15,0:28:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the truth.\NAnd so if I start to take responsibility now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.15,0:28:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and I say,\Nthe way I was looking at this
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.15,0:28:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,set me up for this depression.\NSet me up for this frustration and anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.34,0:28:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Set me up for this let down.\NSet me up for this disappointment.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.73,0:29:02.73,Default,,0,0,0,,The courage then to look at that\Nand be willing to tell the truth about it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.73,0:29:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,now changes the way I feel\Nabout the whole subject.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.73,0:29:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can now move up to a situation\Nwhere I say to myself,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.73,0:29:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,well, it's okay.\NIt's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.18,0:29:19.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how people are taught in this world\Nand I grew up in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.18,0:29:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and I guess I learned the same as everybody.\NBut I'm willing to look at it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.24,0:29:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,in a different way\Nand so we move up to willingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.24,0:29:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The willingness to look at it\Nand say, yes, I agree to look at this.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.24,0:29:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,My intention is up\Nand I see at least the subject
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.24,0:29:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is promising and hopeful.\NThe God of a friendly world
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.30,0:29:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is promising and hopeful.\NIn other words, there's going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.30,0:29:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,some benefit to me\Nnot only in this particular situation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.30,0:29:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's going to be\Na benefit to me as a human being
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.30,0:29:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that will last my lifetime\Nbecause if I solve this one
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.30,0:29:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I've solved it for all time within myself.\NThe willingness to look at that
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.82,0:30:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the willingness to accept\Nwhat I find out
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.82,0:30:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,gives me a certain confidence.\NA certain confidence that there is a process
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.82,0:30:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,going on within me.\NThat this depression has arisen
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.82,0:30:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,to bring something to my attention.\NIt's as though it's saying
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.82,0:30:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,something is out, something is wrong\Nwithin my mind, within my consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.82,0:30:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,within my spiritual position.\NThat's what pain means, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.82,0:30:28.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pain means, please look at me,\Nsomething is out.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.36,0:30:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Pharmacologically we can treat the depression,\Nof course, we can get the person
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.36,0:30:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,out of it temporarily.\NBut the person and his way of being in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.36,0:30:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and the way he's holding who he is\Nand how he relates to the world
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.36,0:30:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and his universe and his expectations\Nis not changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.36,0:30:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So the vulnerability remains the same.\NAnd we know that people who are treated
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.36,0:30:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with just antidepressants\Nwill recover from this episode.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.36,0:30:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NBecause the whole context has not changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.36,0:31:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Without an understanding\Nand depth into the nature of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.36,0:31:04.49,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness itself,\Nthe vulnerability remains.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.49,0:31:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And so the person is subject\Nto repeated bouts of depression
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.49,0:31:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,within their lifetime.\NIn looking at this in a holistic way
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.90,0:31:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,from the viewpoint of body, mind and spirit\Nwe want to address what is the basic cause
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.90,0:31:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to\Nbring about an immunity
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.90,0:31:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,from further episodes\Nof this debilitating experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.19,0:31:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,The acceptance then,\Nmoving into accepting
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.19,0:31:33.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the setup\Nand seeing what the setup is
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.19,0:31:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,without blaming oneself,\Nwithout getting into a make wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.19,0:31:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing wrong with it,\Nit's just that it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.19,0:31:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We've been trained in our world\Nto think that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.19,0:31:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all set up to think that way.\NOur parents were set up to think that way
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.19,0:31:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore they set us up.\NThey just passed it on down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.19,0:31:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,There are several times\Nwhen there's descriptions
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.19,0:32:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of very severe depressions.\NSo it belongs sort of
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.19,0:32:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in the collective consciousness\Nand we all got brainwashed
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.19,0:32:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,with the same programs\Nthat somehow happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.29,0:32:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the source of it\Nis outside oneself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.29,0:32:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You see as we move up here,\Nthe willingness to tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.29,0:32:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the willingness to look at this,\Nwe see the energy fields,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.29,0:32:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the numbers, the power of the field\Nnumbers jump like this
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.29,0:32:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and why is the energy field positive\Ninstead of negative?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.29,0:32:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because above the level of courage\Nthe person has stopped projecting
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.29,0:32:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the source of their happiness\Noutside of themself.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.29,0:32:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The person has begun to re-own\Ntheir own power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.29,0:32:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that the level of courage,\Nthe willingness to tell the truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.29,0:32:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to face with the situation,\Ncope with it and handle it,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.29,0:32:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we see the process going on\Nwithin their power.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.29,0:32:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And by the time we move up\Nto this energy level of acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.29,0:33:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which we see they're a person\Nthat's confident and easy-going,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.29,0:33:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the confidence\Nand easy-goingness coming from?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.29,0:33:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming from the awareness\Nthat I am the source of my happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.29,0:33:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It means that person\Nhas realized by now
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.29,0:33:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in their emotional and psychological\Nand spiritual growth
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.29,0:33:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are the cause\Nof the happiness in their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.29,0:33:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like a person on a desert island\Nsomewhere in the South Pacific
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.29,0:33:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and sail away.\NAnd you come back a year later
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.29,0:33:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll have a coconut factory\Nand they'll be making flutes out of bamboo
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.29,0:33:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and the children will be learning songs\Nand be teaching French to the natives.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.29,0:33:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll find a native girl\Nand build a tree house within the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.29,0:33:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Recreated now for himself\Nthe world around him as an expression
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.42,0:33:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are the source of our own happiness.\NThe anger now,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.42,0:33:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the anger was based on\Na deeper level
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.42,0:33:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is the anger at having sold ourselves out,\Nhaving been sold out,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.42,0:34:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,by having been given this program\Nto operate by
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.42,0:34:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and then find that it doesn't work.\NOur accepting that it doesn't work,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.61,0:34:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,our willingness to look at that\Nand our willingness to change
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.67,0:34:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, okay,\Nbecause how long does it take
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.67,0:34:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,to find a position from which it will work?\NIt only really takes a matter of seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.67,0:34:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How long does it take to come out of depression?\NIt only takes as long as
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.67,0:34:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it takes for one to become willing\Nto look at the truth of what's happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.67,0:34:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you see.\NThe acceptance that that is what has happened
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.70,0:34:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and the realization\Nthat I am the source of my own happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.70,0:34:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that that capacity is within me\Nand my unwillingness
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.70,0:34:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to give it out to the world anymore.\NThe reowning of that power
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.80,0:34:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly you feel\Na state of lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.80,0:34:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly it doesn't matter\Nwhat happens out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.80,0:34:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization of that truth\Nallows you to experience yourself now
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.80,0:34:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,in a far more whole\Nand complete way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.15,0:35:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Not from that lackingness,\Nnot from that vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.15,0:35:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Just this realization\Nthat I am the source,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.15,0:35:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the power to create.\NIt is myself that projected
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.15,0:35:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the meaning onto this.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.28,0:35:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they say one man's meat\Nis another man's poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.28,0:35:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The same event\Nwhich would make one person happy
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.28,0:35:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,is another person happy.\NI have watched people resist
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.28,0:35:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,coming into money for instance\Nbecause it was not within their value system.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.28,0:35:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not what they valued.\NWhat they valued at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.79,0:35:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,was not having money\Nand therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.79,0:35:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you were just giving them a problem.\NWinning the lottery
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.79,0:35:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,might make one person joyful\Nand fill the other one with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.79,0:35:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?\NThe difference is meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.08,0:35:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Who creates the meaning?\NWho gave this something
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.08,0:35:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of oneself\Nthe power and the significance?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.08,0:36:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I am the creator of the meaning.\NI am the one who chooses
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.08,0:36:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,what meaning to give.\NTherefore I have to look at
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.08,0:36:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the way in which I have\Nbought into social consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.08,0:36:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at the values that I have\Nunwittingly allowed myself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.08,0:36:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to be programmed by\Nand say to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.08,0:36:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,do I agree with that?\NAm I willing to give it that same value?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.08,0:36:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization now\Nthat I have the power
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.08,0:36:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to resource myself\Nto recontextualize my life
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.08,0:36:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to see how I have been doing this\Nit brings me a state of inner joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.08,0:36:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The realization that\NI, I alone have the choice now.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.08,0:36:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I have the power.\NI am the one that sets up the meaning
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.08,0:36:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and gives these things\Nthe power over me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.08,0:36:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore it is really possible\Nto come out of disappointment
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.08,0:36:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and grief and sadness\Nand anger about the event
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.11,0:36:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or even indifference\Nto become willing
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.11,0:37:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to really look into it\Nand re-experience my own inner self.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.11,0:37:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually a depressive episode\Neven a brief one
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.11,0:37:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,has within it then\Nactually the potential for joy
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.11,0:37:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because it is something\Ncoming up in our life saying
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.11,0:37:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,look at me, look at me, look at me\Nhere is a mistake that has been causing you
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.11,0:37:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,pain and suffering for endless amounts of time\Nand which will continue to cause you pain
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.11,0:37:27.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and suffering for endless amounts of time.\NYou see that inner state
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.21,0:37:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,of inner joy and serenity\Nreally comes about from a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.21,0:37:35.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of one's own invulnerability\Nand therefore even though the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.30,0:37:39.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is not currently clinically there\Nthe knowledge that one is vulnerable
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.30,0:37:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,precludes\Nthat incredible state
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.30,0:37:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,called the peace of God.\NPeace of God, knowing that one is not
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.30,0:37:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,separated from the source of anything\Nthat one is connected with it
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.30,0:37:55.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that one is one with God.\NHow does one then experience
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.34,0:37:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that which in body, mind and spirit\Nis called spirit?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.91,0:38:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That subtle knowingness\Nit can come from any one of life's
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.36,0:38:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,exigencies\Nfrom any one of life's tragedies
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.36,0:38:12.36,Default,,0,0,0,,even from a minor disappointment.\NAll of these things have within them
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.36,0:38:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the seed\Nthe truth is always present
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.68,0:38:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is the spirit\Nthat which reveals itself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.68,0:38:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the truth\Nthe truth behind consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.68,0:38:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,is always present\Nand therefore can be discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.68,0:38:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at any moment\Nin moments of high joy
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.68,0:38:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in moments of depression\Nand so in Zen they say
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.68,0:38:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,heaven and hell are only a tenth of an inch apart\Nheaven and hell are only a tenth of an inch apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.68,0:38:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I myself of course\Nand I share my own personal experience
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.29,0:38:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that I have experienced\Nand that I have witnessed the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.29,0:38:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of what I am talking about\Nmy own inner experience has been
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.29,0:38:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,a time of great depression\Nsevere depression
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.29,0:39:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,agonizing depression\Nway down in the pits
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.29,0:39:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and from that state\Nof absolute hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.29,0:39:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in which time stopped\Nand the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.29,0:39:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,went on for literally eons\Nbecause you know in a severe depression
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.29,0:39:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,our experience of time\Nis altered
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.29,0:39:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,each second seems like an eternity\Nand so in this depressed state
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.35,0:39:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,time stopped and it went on for eons\Neons and eons
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.35,0:39:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and in these eons\Nthere was no hope
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.35,0:39:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it's almost as if there was a sign\Nin fact that sort of fantasy
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.35,0:39:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the sign that went over the top\Nit said all ye who enter here
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.35,0:39:42.15,Default,,0,0,0,,give up all hope\Nlike Dante's Inferno
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.15,0:39:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,one of the hells\Nand in that experience
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.15,0:39:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of that infinite suffering\Nand agony
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.15,0:39:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and self-hatred\Nthat total feeling of being separated from love
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.15,0:39:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and from God\Ncame a great knowing
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.15,0:40:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly came a great knowing\Nand from that pit
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.15,0:40:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,from those pits of agony\Nsuddenly there was the awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.15,0:40:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,of the infinite presence\Nof eternal love
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.15,0:40:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowingness of truth\Nso the kernel of that is
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.28,0:40:18.28,Default,,0,0,0,,within any experience\Nand once we've investigated
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.28,0:40:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,a thing and found out the truth\Nfor ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.28,0:40:26.31,Default,,0,0,0,,this encourages us to continue to do this\Nto never buy anything
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.31,0:40:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to be detrimental in our life again\Nto use each one of these experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.31,0:40:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to search\Nright into the heart of the matter
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.31,0:40:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to look for what was the fear\Nwhat was the misunderstanding
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.31,0:40:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to do this\Nfrom a viewpoint of forgivingness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.02,0:40:47.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and so essential to this\Nself-healing is the willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.02,0:40:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to love ourself and forgive ourself\Nthe willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.02,0:40:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at our vulnerability\Nand to call it our humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.02,0:40:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the capacity to love\Nour humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:40:59.02,0:41:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for its weaknesses\Nfor its errors
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.02,0:41:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,for its foibles\Nto see that within this humanness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.02,0:41:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,as mistaken as it might be\Nthere was an intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.82,0:41:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,you see once we get off the anger\Nabout our expectation
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.82,0:41:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fact that it didn't work out\Nbecause it can't in a changing world
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.82,0:41:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a world\Nin which there is only one thing
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.82,0:41:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that is certain in the phenomenal\Naspects of this world and its expression
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.82,0:41:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as we experience it\Nand that is that all things change
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.98,0:41:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,look at that\Nall things change
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.98,0:41:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,all things change within human experience\Nbecause human experience is
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.98,0:41:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,that of change\Nif all things change
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.01,0:41:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing remains the same\Nthen to place the source of your happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.01,0:41:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,outside of yourself\Non that which changes
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.01,0:41:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it's only a matter of time\Nbefore the depression ensues
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.04,0:42:00.04,Default,,0,0,0,,is that not correct\Nand not appearing
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.04,0:42:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,coming and going and changing\Nthen the vulnerability is ever present
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.62,0:42:08.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that simple mistake\Nwhich we all make
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.62,0:42:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,which is common to the whole human condition\Nwhich we are trying to look through today
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.65,0:42:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,arises out of something\Nthat is also the same in all of us
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.65,0:42:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and which can be rediscovered\Nand rediscovered right in the pain
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.65,0:42:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of this experience\Nand that is the intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.65,0:42:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness itself\Nthe intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.65,0:42:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of the inner self\Nand this we can see
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.87,0:42:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in two different ways\None by reaching that state
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.87,0:42:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,of compassion\Nand compassion ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.87,0:42:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by reaching such a level of consciousness\Nthat we literally see into the hearts of others
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.87,0:42:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and we just see and know\Nthat innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.26,0:42:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the other way is to\Nthrough introspection
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.26,0:42:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,look and see how this arose\Nwe notice in the child
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.96,0:43:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we notice the innocence of the child\Nthe young child we say
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.96,0:43:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is innocent\Nand what do we mean by that
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.96,0:43:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we mean that he is trusting\Nhe has faith in the integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.96,0:43:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of those around him\Nit never dawns on the child's mind
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.96,0:43:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to doubt the truth\Nof that which is being told
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.96,0:43:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so the young child loves the parents\Nand those extensions of the parent
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.96,0:43:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,called teacher\Nother family members
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.96,0:43:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,peers\Nplaymates
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.18,0:43:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,television\Ncommercials
Dialogue: 0,0:43:34.18,0:43:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the child looks at a commercial\Nas though it's just as truthful
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.86,0:43:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,as its parent\Nbecause of its trustingness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.86,0:43:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its openness\Nbecause of its lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.92,0:43:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because of its lack of paranoia\Nyou might say
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.98,0:43:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's easily programmed\Nand therefore it begins to buy
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.98,0:43:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,out of its innocence\Nthat which it hears
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.98,0:44:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,or that religious group\Netc.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.27,0:44:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and we don't like people that do this\Nand we don't like people that do that
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.27,0:44:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and we don't like people that vote that way\Nand the child's identification with those
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.56,0:44:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that he loves is family\Nthe programs start coming in
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.56,0:44:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,so the innocence of the child now\Ngets programmed
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.56,0:44:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,why? because of its innocence\Nit's because of its innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.56,0:44:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that it buys such statements as\Nall of us Jeffersons are allergic
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.56,0:44:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,heart disease runs in our family\Nwe all have a weight problem in our family
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.56,0:44:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and all these negative programs now\Nare bought out of the child's innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.56,0:44:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we might say\Nthe child is like the hardware of a computer
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.10,0:44:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the hardware of the computer\Nwill play any software program
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.10,0:44:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,that's put through it\Nand yet the nature of the hardware
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.71,0:44:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the nature of that which is\Ntruly the computer itself
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.71,0:44:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is unchanged\Nno matter what floppy disk we play
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.71,0:45:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter what software\Nwhat programs we play through the computer
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.71,0:45:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,its intrinsic innocence\Nits purity, its integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.71,0:45:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,has not been sullied\Nit has not changed at all
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.71,0:45:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we take out all the programs\Nwhich are erroneous
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.71,0:45:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and the hardware remains the same\Nthe same with consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.74,0:45:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that childlike consciousness\Nwith its innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.74,0:45:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with its purity of motive\Nwith its capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.74,0:45:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to remain pure\Nno matter what the programs may be
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.74,0:45:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,remains essential and unchanged\Nit is exactly what is listening
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.22,0:45:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to my voice right now\Nit is that childlike consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.26,0:45:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in all its purity and innocence\Nthat is what's listening
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.26,0:45:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to this voice right now\Nnot the person
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.38,0:45:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,not the personality\Nbut that consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.38,0:45:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,in all its pure and simple purity\Neven if that which is listening
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.25,0:45:58.25,Default,,0,0,0,,says I don't believe a word of it\Nwhere does I don't believe
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.25,0:46:02.25,Default,,0,0,0,,a word of it come from\Nit comes from another word
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.25,0:46:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,another belief system\Nthat the child bought out of innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.25,0:46:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the father says don't trust anybody\Nor
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.50,0:46:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,some disappointing experience\Nsets up the program within the child's mind
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.50,0:46:19.08,Default,,0,0,0,,don't trust anything you hear\Nso if you're saying to yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.08,0:46:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe anything he says\Nyou're saying that because out of the childlike innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.08,0:46:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,you bought that program\Nthe way to be secure in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.08,0:46:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is don't believe anything you hear\Nor you'll be misled and led down the primrose path
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.21,0:46:35.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but the nature of the innocence\Nyou bought that program remains the same
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.21,0:46:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,is it not\Nbecause it's not the mind right this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.21,0:46:43.21,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to listen to the truth\Ndiscern that which is the truth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.21,0:46:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,out of its hopefulness\Nout of its trustingness
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.21,0:46:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,hoping to hear that which will be helpful\Nthat which will nurture life
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.21,0:46:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that which will relieve suffering\Nand so you see that intrinsic innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.43,0:46:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so that when you look within yourself now\Ninto the self healing
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.43,0:47:03.43,Default,,0,0,0,,into the understanding\Nof what was the program that was set up
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.43,0:47:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to re-own that innocence\Nin all spiritual work
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.43,0:47:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it is so crucial\Nin all work in psychological research
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.56,0:47:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself\Nand introspection
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.56,0:47:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to always keep within your awareness\Nthat whatever you bought
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.56,0:47:23.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you bought out of the beauty of what you are\Nyou bought it out of your own love
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.85,0:47:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and your own trustingness\Nand you really bought it out of your own integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.85,0:47:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,because you projected your own integrity\Nonto the world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.85,0:47:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,and thought this is a place that you can trust and believe anything you hear\Nbecause that is where you were coming from
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.85,0:47:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,until you got programmed\Nthat sometimes it is very useful to lie
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.85,0:47:43.85,Default,,0,0,0,,sometimes it is useful\Nto tell them the check is in the mail
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.85,0:47:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,we all know that one\Nwe got programmed into the idea
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.91,0:47:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that the only way you can survive\Nas a body in this world
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.91,0:47:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,is you have to\Ntailor the truth a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.91,0:48:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,create a business\Nbusiness ethics
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.46,0:48:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but didn't we buy that out of our own innocence\Nwe thought
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.46,0:48:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what they say\Nyou got to do in this world to survive
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.46,0:48:12.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so I guess I got to do that\Nand of course when you do that
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.46,0:48:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,you pay the price\Nanytime we go below the line
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.46,0:48:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we pay the price\Nand the price is we lose our power
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.46,0:48:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of power within the world\Nso that's what the anger is about
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.62,0:48:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost my power\Nthe source of my happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.62,0:48:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,will never be returned to me\Nbecause it is outside of myself
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.62,0:48:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I projected it out there\Nthe healing of it then comes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.62,0:48:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,from the willingness\Nto look at the truth of this
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.71,0:48:44.71,Default,,0,0,0,,to say to myself\Nout of my innocence
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.71,0:48:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,like other humans on this planet\Nlike most of us in fact
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.81,0:48:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I brought a certain way of looking at life\Nin which the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.81,0:48:57.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is first of all\Noutside of myself
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.26,0:49:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,secondly it's always in the future\Nthe separation from the source of happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.26,0:49:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,is not only in space\Nbut it's also in time
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.26,0:49:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow or the next day\Nor next week
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.26,0:49:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or the year after\Nor when I finally graduate
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.96,0:49:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,when I reach middle age\Nor when I get that big house
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.96,0:49:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,or when I get that Cadillac\Nit's always in the future
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.96,0:49:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,so we're always separated\Nfrom the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.96,0:49:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and we never feel complete\Nthe realization that we are the source of our happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.96,0:49:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we can create it at any second\Ngives us a sense of completion
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.73,0:49:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of completion then\Nso that it can be cut off at any second
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.79,0:49:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and feel complete\Nif we suddenly stop this talk
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.79,0:49:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,right now\Nit is complete right as of this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.79,0:49:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,I have with the best of my ability\Nsaid exactly what I wanted to say
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.79,0:49:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,not feeling I'm going to say it in a minute\Nnot saying it's going to come tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.79,0:49:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but right now\Nbeing with the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:49:58.79,0:50:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of experiencing the joy\Nof doing the best I can at this moment
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.79,0:50:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and so\Nthe joyfulness then
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.82,0:50:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,accompanies the experience\Nthere is no
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.89,0:50:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,tomorrow about it\Nbecause of the sense of completion then
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.05,0:50:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,whether someone enjoys the talk\Nis immaterial
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.05,0:50:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that is frosting on the cake\Nbut it is not part and parcel
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.46,0:50:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,what one does in the world\Nhas to be accompanied by
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.46,0:50:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the sense of completion\Nin the doing of it itself
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.46,0:50:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,so that the payoff is not something\Nwhich is an aside
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.46,0:50:39.46,Default,,0,0,0,,which is something as separate\Nfrom the doingness
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.46,0:50:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience of it right now\Nthe completion is with
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.46,0:50:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencing right now\Nnot something separate from it
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.88,0:50:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in that then one is aware\Nof the lovingness of all experience
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.88,0:50:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,that is the way one is\Nwith the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.88,0:50:59.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the loving of life\Nthen in all its expressions
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.88,0:51:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the loving of life in all its expressions\Nincluding its disappointments
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.88,0:51:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,its ups and downs\Nthe continual
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.88,0:51:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,process of making the mistake\Nand learning from the mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.55,0:51:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,so that is nothing but a mistake then\Nyou might say depression
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.55,0:51:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,is nature's way of saying to us\NGod's way of saying to us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.55,0:51:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,our own psychology's way of saying\Nit to us however
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.55,0:51:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,looking at it\Nis okay with you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.55,0:51:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it's our psychological way\Nour biologic way
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.55,0:51:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,our spiritual way\Nit's our body our mind and our spirit
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.55,0:51:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,saying look what's out\Nthere needs to be fixed
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.55,0:51:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,please understand me\Nout of your compassion heal
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.55,0:51:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,heal me heal all of us\Nwhich leads to the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.84,0:51:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is this inner sense of separation\Nthat
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.19,0:51:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I will not be complete and whole\Nunless I become united with something
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.19,0:52:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,out there\Nthis brings up the difference
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.29,0:52:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,in the precipitating event\Nthat leads to suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.29,0:52:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,or depression\Nvery often between men and women
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.29,0:52:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,men experience the presence of God\Nwithin them or the connection to God
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.29,0:52:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and very often in the form of power\Nwe remember that the three
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.29,0:52:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,classical attributes\Nof God are omnipresence
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.29,0:52:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,omniscience omnipotence\Nso that God is often
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.29,0:52:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,experienced in the unconscious\Nof men as connection
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.29,0:52:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,with power so that power\Nbecomes that
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.29,0:52:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which they seek and therefore\Nthe precipitating event
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.64,0:52:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,very often in men\Nleads to the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.64,0:52:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,was feeling separated\Nfrom the source of one's power
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.64,0:52:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in this case the power has been put out\Ninto the world so it would be
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.64,0:52:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,the loss of a title\Nloss of a position loss of a business
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.64,0:52:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of the status\Nsymbols that signify that power
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.64,0:53:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and so that sense of\Nseparation that vulnerability
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.18,0:53:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,because it has not been really healed\Nremains there
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.18,0:53:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore money position and power\Nbecome their traditional goals
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.18,0:53:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of men\Nwomen experience in the unconscious
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.57,0:53:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,their connection with God\Nmore in the form of love
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.57,0:53:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so that relationships are all important\Nand the experience of love
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.57,0:53:26.57,Default,,0,0,0,,through the relationship\Nwe remember the example
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.57,0:53:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,of the old woman who sat in the rocking chair\Nrocking back and forth staring hopelessly
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.57,0:53:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,out the window\Nit was because of feeling cut off
Dialogue: 0,0:53:34.57,0:53:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,from a relationship and she experienced\Nthat lovingness
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.57,0:53:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,coming through that relationship\Nand so the interruption of the relationship
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.57,0:53:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,then was the precipitating factor\Nand so we see that the basic
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.57,0:53:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,problem is still the same\Nit's just that it takes different form
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.57,0:53:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,different expression\Nbetween the two sexes
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.57,0:53:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,depression leads us into\Nsomething we mentioned in the beginning of the film
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.57,0:54:02.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole subject of suicide\Nwhen we look at suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.63,0:54:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll see that\Nwhat is desired is not
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.63,0:54:10.63,Default,,0,0,0,,really death of the body\Nwhat is desired is relief
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.63,0:54:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from suffering\Nthe realization that that is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.70,0:54:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what is sought\Nrelief from suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.70,0:54:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,see the body did not create the dilemma\Nthe body cannot experience the dilemma
Dialogue: 0,0:54:22.70,0:54:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore the idea\Nthat if I get rid of the body
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.70,0:54:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I will get rid of the source\Nis fallacious
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.70,0:54:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the body neither created it\Nnor did it experience it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.70,0:54:38.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole problem is going on within consciousness\Ntherefore the solution is within consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.70,0:54:42.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to look at\Nthe nature of consciousness itself
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.70,0:54:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and see that that is where it arose\Nand that is where it is being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.70,0:54:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore that is\Nwhere it has to be solved
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.92,0:54:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the solution is to realize\Nthat what is desired is the relief
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.92,0:54:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,from suffering\Nand in the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:54:59.53,0:55:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,which identifies itself with the body\Nand thinks I am a body
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.53,0:55:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,then the loss of the energy\Nof life due to the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.53,0:55:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the person is dispirited\Nleads to a decrease
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.53,0:55:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of energy\Nand we have the forms
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.53,0:55:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the many forms of passive suicide\NI would say that
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.53,0:55:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the majority of deaths in the United States\Nin the world in fact
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.53,0:55:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,are really forms of passive suicide\Nthe loss of that sense of aliveness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.53,0:55:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that excitement\Nand commitment to life
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.53,0:55:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and the passive suicide\Nthen takes many forms
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.53,0:55:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,statistically it shows up\Nas the automobile accident
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.53,0:55:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what is passive suicide\Nreally failure to get out of the way
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.53,0:55:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of the bus isn't it\Nfor some reason we just didn't care enough
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.53,0:55:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the precautions\Nwe didn't care enough
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.53,0:55:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to love our life\Nwe didn't value it enough
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.53,0:55:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,to care for ourself to preserve it\Nand so passive suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.53,0:56:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,takes the form of the person\Nwho ignores their physical disease
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.53,0:56:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the diabetic who just\Ndoesn't care to stay on
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.53,0:56:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the diet\Ndoesn't care to take the insulin
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.10,0:56:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly goes into\Ninsulin reactions and overdoses
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.10,0:56:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and diabetic coma\N3, 4, 5 times in the hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.10,0:56:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,in diabetic coma until they leave\Nin the addictions
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.26,0:56:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,we see that in the form of the overdose\Ntraditionally the overdose
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.26,0:56:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the person who is taking\Nmultiple drugs for 20 years
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.26,0:56:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and then dies of an overdose\Nhow could that be a miscalculation
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.26,0:56:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,there are experts on psychopharmacology\Nthey've dosed themselves thousands
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.26,0:56:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and thousands of times\Nit's called an accident
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.39,0:56:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no such thing as an accident\Nthe automobile accident
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.13,0:56:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,where the person was just careless\Nwhat we really see is a loss
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.13,0:56:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of desire to live\Nis that not so
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.13,0:57:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the failure to heed health advice\Nthe failure to take care of one's health
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.13,0:57:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the failure to take care of one's assets\Nall indicating a loss
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.13,0:57:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of that energy\Nthat sense of aliveness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.13,0:57:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from deflated\Nfirst entrapped
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.13,0:57:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,deflated then dispirited\Nthen the loss of energy
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.13,0:57:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and then unconsciously\Nseeking a way out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.13,0:57:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,so that one doesn't have to feel guilty\None doesn't have to feel guilty
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.13,0:57:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that they died of diabetic coma\None didn't bother to alter one's lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.13,0:57:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to prevent that coronary heart attack\Nif we realize
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.13,0:57:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that what we want\Nis the relief of suffering
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.13,0:57:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then the relief of suffering\Ncomes about through an understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.13,0:57:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,of the nature of consciousness itself\Nthrough the processes
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.13,0:57:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have described in this talk\Nthe willingness
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.13,0:57:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,to experience out\Nand it can be experienced out
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.13,0:57:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,all the symptoms\Nthat are being experienced
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.13,0:58:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the looking at one's life\Nand using a technique
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.13,0:58:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I call the worst scenario\Nto sit down and look at your life
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.13,0:58:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and say\Nwhat is the worst possible outcome
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.13,0:58:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the feeling\Nthat comes up with that
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.13,0:58:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and so resisting that feeling\Nto constantly cancel out
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.13,0:58:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,the thoughts about it\Nand instead handle the feeling directly
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.13,0:58:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and as we do that\Nwe'll notice that the symptoms
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.13,0:58:29.13,Default,,0,0,0,,begin to abate\Nwe come out of the depression
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.13,0:58:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we're willing to look at the fear\Nwe're willing to look at the way
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.13,0:58:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that this was set up\Nhow we got set up
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.13,0:58:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,our anger about that\Nusing the energy of the anger
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.13,0:58:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to want something better for ourselves\Nwhat it really means then
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.70,0:58:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is we have to recontextualize\Nour whole life
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.70,0:58:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to look at everything\Nand say to ourself
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.70,0:58:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I hold this\Nso that it will have a value
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.70,0:59:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that is great enough\Nthat if it left my life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.70,0:59:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I would still have that\Nwhich is worth living for
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.70,0:59:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,to what about this\Ncan I dedicate my life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.70,0:59:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what about my job\Ngives it meaning and significance
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.70,0:59:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,how can I see it in such a way\Nthat my value as a human being
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.70,0:59:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,will not be changed\Nif that should leave my life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.70,0:59:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and so we have to look at our goals\Nand our motives
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.70,0:59:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what are we willing to dedicate\Nour life to
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.70,0:59:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what does have significant meaning\Nservice to others
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.70,0:59:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,even if we lost all capacity\Nto serve our own life
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.70,0:59:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the meaning then\Nof being of service to others
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.70,0:59:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we see people of course\Nhave all kinds of disfigurations
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.70,0:59:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of losses\Nand they go on
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.70,0:59:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,somehow life still has meaning to them\Nwhat does that mean
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.70,0:59:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,does it mean we are weaker than they are\Nthat morally they are superior
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.70,1:00:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,no, it means that somehow\Nthey have sensed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.70,1:00:05.70,Default,,0,0,0,,some greater meaning in their life\Nthey had to let go of a lesser meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.70,1:00:09.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and find a greater meaning\Nso that is what depression means to us
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.70,1:00:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it means that we settled\Nfor a smaller meaning
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.70,1:00:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,less than the truth\Nwe have to re-examine
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.70,1:00:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and see what was the true meaning\Nof that in our life
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.70,1:00:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,what about our life makes it worthwhile\Neven without that
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.70,1:00:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,direction by asking ourselves\Na very simple question
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.70,1:00:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we can do this as we go about\Nour daily life
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.70,1:00:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,growing in consciousness\Nis something that we do
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.31,1:00:42.31,Default,,0,0,0,,as we go about our everyday business\Nand we ask ourselves
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.31,1:00:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,the question\NI couldn't live if I didn't have blank
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.86,1:00:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,life wouldn't be worth living\Nunless
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.43,1:00:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we fill in\Nwhat in our own mind
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.82,1:00:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,we have put in that blank space\Nwhere is our vulnerabilities
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.82,1:01:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,our vulnerabilities\Nare where we think
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.82,1:01:08.10,Default,,0,0,0,,we couldn't live without that\Nwhat if we put our survival on
Dialogue: 0,1:01:08.10,1:01:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,so the whole technique then\Nis to first find out
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.10,1:01:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,where the areas of vulnerability lie\Nsit down and picture
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.26,1:01:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we go about\Nthe process of
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.55,1:01:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,letting go, resisting\Nall the feelings that come up
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.55,1:01:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and ask your own inner consciousness\Nask your own unconscious
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.74,1:01:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,ask the God within you\Nask your super consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.80,1:01:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,however it is\Nask your intuition
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.80,1:01:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,however you hold that inner questioning\Nand you begin an inner questioning search
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.99,1:01:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,all of us have to do that\Nwhat is the meaning of our life
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.99,1:01:55.43,Default,,0,0,0,,what is it's significance\Nis worth living for? What do we value that is greater than that which is limited and temporary?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.03,1:02:11.58,Default,,0,0,0,,By removing all these things one by one, we find that that who we are is growing in stature.\NWe're no longer so vulnerable to external events because there's always two things going on.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.54,1:02:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There is the event out there as we see it in ordinary consciousness happening out there,\Nand then there is how we feel about that, and how we feel about it depends on our attitudes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.30,1:02:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We can decide how we want to be with that. See, that who we are then and what its relationship\Nis to that event, see? So I am one thing and the event is something else, and I have power over
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.86,1:02:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,how I want to hold that, how I want to value that relationship, how I want to picture it,\Nand whether I'm willing to give it the power over my life. Am I willing to give money enough power
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.90,1:03:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,over my life, that if I lose it, I no longer desire to live? Am I willing to give a relationship that\Npower over my life? Am I willing to give possessions, titles, degrees, cars? Think of all
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.38,1:03:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that people put and value greater than their own life and you see the enormous vulnerability.\NIt's high up there within the most important causes of death,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.28,1:03:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and especially so in adolescence.\NSo what does it say about the values, then, that we're teaching our adolescents?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.94,1:03:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the transitory things that we're telling them to base their life on?\NWe have to reevaluate for ourself what is the importance,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.62,1:03:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the meaning of our life,\Nwhat do we hold of sufficient value that it will preserve us
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.48,1:04:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in the face of any kind of a loss.\NOut of this inner understanding, then, comes a reevaluation of that relationship
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.81,1:04:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,between body, mind, and spirit.\NBecause it is mind, then, that is setting our goals and our purposes.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.91,1:04:15.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If we begin to question our values, reevaluate our position with them,\Nwhether we like it or not,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.57,1:04:19.49,Default,,0,0,0,,whether we like the term or not,\Nwe're really doing that which is called spiritual work.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.21,1:04:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What is spirit?\NWhat is it, that energy of life itself?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.33,1:04:33.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, we have a decision about its form.\NWe can decide what to give meaning to, what to give value to.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:35.05,1:04:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Within that energy field called consciousness, then, we have great freedom.\NWe have great freedom.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.43,1:04:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It is up to our own inner choice.\NBy seeing that, by merely seeing,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.81,1:04:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have the choice of what we want to give value to,\Nwe reown our power.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:51.65,1:04:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We move up on the chart.\NWe move up from victim to source.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.49,1:05:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to accept back our own power, which we have given to the world.\NWith that comes an inner state of serenity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.01,1:05:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,An inner state of serenity that I am experiencing the value of my existence,\Nthat I need no proof.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.19,1:05:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The world doesn't have to do anything.\NI don't need to bring home the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.53,1:05:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't need to bring home any trophies to give it value,\Nbecause I see its value within myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.59,1:05:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I see and I treasure and I hold sacred the value of life itself.\NNo trophies are needed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:29.73,1:05:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I accept that which is given me with thanks.\NWith gratitude, I hold the essence of that which I am,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.50,1:05:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,without asking that the world give me back anything that I've demanded of it.\NIn doing that,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.91,1:05:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,we move into an invulnerable position.\NWe're no longer prone to these disappointments, the anger, the rage,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.23,1:06:03.57,Default,,0,0,0,,turning against ourself and the thoughts of suicide,\Nthat hopeless, fallacious idea that by killing the body,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:03.57,1:06:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we will kill the source of our suffering.\NBy owning that we ourselves are the source of our suffering,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.53,1:06:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,we transcend it.\NBy transcending it, we bring about that inner healing,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.13,1:06:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the purpose of today's talk.\NThank you.
